        "id": 1002605
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-08T06:18:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "offset + length can overflow because both values are uint32_t. A large offset could pass these checks and make the later memcpy read outside componentImage. Could we calculate this in uint64_t and validate offset before doing any pointer arithmetic? Please also add a wraparound test.",
      "revId": "115799f70b01d9c895aa32179dc2716c59144812",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8fca9c00_87d73029",
        "filename": "fw-update/package_parser.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 122
      },
      "lineNbr": 252,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002605
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-08T06:18:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The new iterator no longer performs some checks enforced by the old decoder, such as rejecting zero image offsets or sizes, empty versions, and invalid comparison-stamp options. Could we restore these validations and add negative tests for them?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 252,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 252,
        "endChar": 53
      },
      "revId": "115799f70b01d9c895aa32179dc2716c59144812",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "754f1162_5d40afa6",
        "filename": "fw-update/package_parser.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 122
      },
      "lineNbr": 259,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002605
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-08T06:18:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This creates a separate copy of the image for every component entry. The iterator allows multiple entries to resolve to the same offset and size, so one payload could be copied many times and exhaust BMC memory. Could we retain views into the package, or explicitly validate or deduplicate repeated image ranges?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 257,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 259,
        "endChar": 76
      },
      "revId": "115799f70b01d9c895aa32179dc2716c59144812",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6b8fe6b6_bf919559",
        "filename": "fw-update/update_manager.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 122
      },
      "lineNbr": 171,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002605
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-08T06:18:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "associatePkgToDevices() can return multiple records for the same EID, but this map stores only one and ignores failed emplace() calls. This could silently skip updates while still reporting success.\nCould we preserve or serialize every matched record and check the insertion result?\n\nThe same issue also exists in the corresponding deviceUpdaterMap.emplace(...) inside processStream().",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 168,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 171,
        "endChar": 79
      },
      "revId": "115799f70b01d9c895aa32179dc2716c59144812",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "475b6914_523bb9da",
        "filename": "fw-update/update_manager.cpp",
